Compass and Sass

Compass is collection of css files. It provides

   1. A command line tool for managing your Sass projects.
   2. Simple integration with Ruby-on-Rails, Merb, StaticMatic, and even non-ruby application servers.
   3. Loads of Sass mixins to make building your website a snap.
   
Installation

1. Install the below gem
     gem install compass

2. Run the below line
	compass init rails

3. Add the following to your environment.rb:

    config.gem "compass", :version => ">= 0.11.1"

Then, make sure you restart your server. 


